        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "\n\n\t\t\t\t\t \n\n                 \t\n\n\n\t « All Events\n\n\t\n\tThis event has passed.\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\tICONS: A Panel Discussion\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\tMay 14, 2026 @ 1:00 pm - 2:30 pm\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tIn this panel discussion, four iconic Canadian women discuss their personal journeys to their positions as leaders in their chosen fields and reflect on how being a woman has helped or hindered their progressions. Moderated by Elizabeth May, this hopeful discussion prompts speakers on how they succeeded to where they are today, their visions and hopes for the future, and their advice to women aiming to succeed in our 21st century world.\nIcons is presented in concurrence with Homage, a unique, beautiful and powerful exhibition of 40 tailor-made and exquisite necklaces designed and created for 40 of Canada’s most iconic women. Through design and choice of material, each piece celebrates the achievements, talents, perseverance and character of their dedicated icon, and is accompanied by a biography and a drawing of each woman. Homage celebrates influential Canadian women and shines a light on how they continue to shape our country in the face of new challenges and changes in attitudes toward women in society.\nPanelists:\nBrenna Corner, Artistic Director of Pacific Opera; Natalie Telewiak, Principal Architect at MG Architecture in Vancouver; Dr. Shazhan Amed, Clinical Researcher and Paediatric Endocrinologist at BC Children’s Hospital\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\n\n\n\n\t Details \n\t\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\tDate:\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t May 14, 2026 \n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\tTime:\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t1:00 pm - 2:30 pm\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\tEvent Categories: ArtSpring Presents, ArtSpring Presents 2025-26, Gallery Exhibits & Events\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t